    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Instruments for execution by beheading. They operate by means of a heavy blade falling between two grooved posts. These were used particularly during the French Revolution, but also in Belgium, Germany, Sweden and some Swiss cantons.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
